# JSON/YAML Configuration Standards

## JSON Standards

- Use consistent indentation (2 spaces)
- Use double quotes for strings
- No trailing commas
- Validate JSON syntax before committing
- Use meaningful property names

## YAML Standards

- Use 2 spaces for indentation
- Use consistent quote style
- Use `---` document separators when needed
- Avoid tabs (use spaces)
- Use consistent list style (dash or bracket)

## Configuration Best Practices

- Validate schema when possible
- Document required fields
- Provide default values when appropriate
- Use environment variables for secrets
- Keep configs version-controlled (except secrets)

## Schema Validation

- Use JSON Schema for JSON files
- Validate against schemas in CI
- Document schema changes
- Version schemas appropriately

## Security

- Never commit secrets in config files
- Use `.example` files for templates
- Document required environment variables
- Validate sensitive fields are not committed

## Configuration Checklist

- [ ] Valid syntax (JSON/YAML)
- [ ] No secrets committed
- [ ] Schema validated (if applicable)
- [ ] Documented required fields
- [ ] Example files provided
